  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How I recover my Facebook password?",
  "response": "To recover your Facebook password, follow these steps:\n\n1. **Go to the Facebook login page**: Open your web browser and navigate to the Facebook homepage.\n\n2. **Click on \"Forgotten password?\"**: Below the login fields, you will see a link that says \"Forgotten password?\". Click on it.\n\n3. **Enter your email address or phone number**: You will be prompted to enter the email address or phone number associated with your Facebook account. Type it in and click \"Search\".\n\n4. **Choose a recovery method**: Facebook will offer you several ways to reset your password:\n   - **Via Email**: If you choose this option, you will receive an email from Facebook with a link to reset your password. Click on the link, follow the instructions, and enter a new password.\n   - **Via SMS**: If you choose this option, you will receive a text message with a code. Enter the code on the Facebook page, and then you can set a new password.\n   - **Via a Trusted Contact**: If you have set up trusted contacts, you can request a recovery code from them. Follow the on-screen instructions to get the code and reset your password.\n\n5. **Reset your password**: Once you have chosen your recovery method and followed the necessary steps, you will be able to enter a new password. Make sure it is strong and secure.\n\n6. **Log in with your new password**: After resetting your password, return to the login page and enter your email address and new password to access your account.\n\nIf you encounter any issues during this process, you can visit the Facebook Help Center for more detailed instructions or contact their support team for further assistance.",
